text: Map of Lang Parish, Poole County, New South Wales.Lang, New South Wales, is a remote civil parish of Poole County in far northwest New South Wales./ Map of the County of Poole : Western Division, , located at 29°30′25″S 141°31′10″E. The geography of the parish is mostly the flat, arid landscape of the Channel Country. The parish has a Köppen climate classification of BWh (Hot desert). (direct: Final Revised Paper) The County is barely inhabited with a population density of less than 1 person per 150 km² and the landscape is a flat arid scrubland. ==References== Category:Parishes of Poole County Category:Far West (New South Wales)
title: Parish of Lang
